  "description": "The two-door refrigerator of the Polish company Amica belongs to mid-range solutions. It provides a traditional layout for models with two compartments, in which the freezer is located at the bottom. Useful features of the unit include support for automatic defrosting Total NoFrost. With a height of 180 cm, the Amica FK 299.2FTZ refrigerator holds up to 250 liters in total, of which 70 liters is the usable volume of the freezer compartment. There are three drawers here. The maximum freezing capacity is about 4 kg, and the autonomous cold storage time is 19 hours. The 180-liter refrigerator compartment assumes a FreshZone freshness zone, “sharpened” for storing meat and fish. Of the pleasant additions to the interior space, there is a metal hanging shelf for two bottles. The controls are represented by a touch panel, which is located inside. The energy class of the unit corresponds to an A + rating (up to 255 kWh of electricity per year of operation), and the noise level can reach 42 dB.",
